(engineering
  :doc "MOTOI-NO-NETWORKS-GUARD"
  :date "2026-07-17"
  :author "auto — hook author"
  :audience ("agents" "alfred" "future-motoi-team")
  :dialect "motoi"
  :confidentiality "internal"
  :training-eligible false
  :provenance "authored in response to loam-client 2026-07-17 doctrine violation"

  :originating-doctrine
"Alfred, 2026-07-17: \"Motoi cannot connect to networks. Ever.\"

Composes with the memory-index entries:
  - project_motoi_no_tools_no_internet_2026_07_17
    (Motoi is hermetic. No fetch, no shell, no function-calling, no external
     APIs. `http/serve` is a SERVER, not a client. `llm/*` verbs point at a
     LOCAL model server and are fine.)
  - project_sakura_internet_business_posture_2026_07_17
    (Sakura is the business-side dialect and CAN reach the internet. When
     authoring new verbs, ASK 'Motoi or Sakura?' first. If the verb needs
     the network, it belongs in ~/code/sakura-scheme/, not here.)

The 2026-07-17 loam-client incident: an agent authored
`motoi-scheme/lib/net/loam-client.js` despite explicit in-lane guards
telling it not to. The files were preserved (no-deletes doctrine) at
_archive-doctrine-violation-loam-client-2026-07-17/ and this hook was
authored so the class of violation is caught at the git-commit boundary,
not after."

  :what-the-hook-enforces
"Two independent guards, both fired by the same pre-commit invocation:

 GUARD 1 — lib/net/ allow-list

   The ONLY file allowed under lib/net/ is `http-serve.js` (the HTTP
   server — Motoi serves; Motoi does not fetch).

   Any staged Added/Copied/Modified file whose path matches ^lib/net/
   and whose basename is not on the allow-list is rejected.

   Files whose basename matches ^[^/]*-client\\.[A-Za-z0-9]+$ get a
   specialized 'LOAM-flavored' rejection message that names the archive
   MANIFEST.slat as prior art — this is exactly the shape of the
   2026-07-17 loam-client violation.

 GUARD 2 — HTTP-client source-line patterns

   Scans ADDED lines only (via `git diff --cached -U0`) for staged files
   under lib/ or src/ with extensions .js .mjs .cjs .ts .mts .cts, matching
   case-insensitively:

     - fetch(\"http... / fetch('http... / fetch(`http...
     - axios.  /  axios(
     - require('node-fetch') / require(\"node-fetch\") / import ... from 'node-fetch'
     - http.request( / https.request( / http.get( / https.get( / .post(
     - net.createConnection( / net.Socket(
     - new WebSocket(
     - Any string literal matching https?://<host>
       where <host> is NOT 127.0.0.1, localhost, or 0.0.0.0

   Comments are ignored (lines whose first non-whitespace character is
   //, #, /*, *, or */).

 EXCEPTIONS

   - lib/net/http-serve.js is allow-listed unconditionally.
   - lib/ai/llm.js is exempt from Guard 2 (approved local-LLM curl
     exception per project_motoi_no_tools_no_internet_2026_07_17:
     'llm/* verbs FINE (points at local model server)').
   - Loopback URLs (127.0.0.1, localhost, 0.0.0.0) always pass the
     string-literal check.

 FAST PATH

   If `git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=ACM` returns no path
   matching ^(lib|src)/, the hook exits 0 immediately. Measured 35ms on a
   real ~180-file staged working set."

  :install
"Repo-scoped, no global side effects.

  bash scripts/install-hooks.sh

  # -> sets: git config core.hooksPath .githooks

Verify:

  git config core.hooksPath
  # -> .githooks

Uninstall (if ever needed):

  git config --unset core.hooksPath"

  :override
"`git commit --no-verify` bypasses ALL pre-commit hooks. Alfred's CLAUDE.md
is explicit: 'No --force, no --no-verify.' Git offers no reliable way for
a pre-commit hook to detect --no-verify (the hook simply isn't invoked in
that case); the README.md and the hook itself carry the doctrinal warning
as the only defense."

