    (("/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/.githooks/pre-commit"
      :role "the hook"
      :size-bytes 9741
      :executable true)
     ("/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/.githooks/README.md"
      :role "install + bypass docs")
     ("/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/scripts/install-hooks.sh"
      :role "one-liner: git config core.hooksPath .githooks"
      :executable true
      :note "was previously a delegate-to-lacuna-git-hooks stub; that path was
             never wired up in this repo. .githooks/ is authoritative now.")
     ("/Users/alfred/code/motoi-scheme/tests/hooks/pre-commit.test.mjs"
      :role "node --test suite (9 cases)"))

  :test-fixture-results
"Run: node --test tests/hooks/pre-commit.test.mjs
Result: 9 passed, 0 failed, ~1.3s total.

Cases:
  1. fast path — commit touching neither lib/ nor src/ passes                 PASS
  2. lib/net/http-serve.js — allow-listed, modifying it passes                PASS
  3. lib/net/loam-client.js — REJECTED with loam-flavored message             PASS
     - stderr matched: 'LOAM-flavored violation'
     - stderr matched: '_archive-doctrine-violation-loam-client-2026-07-17'
     - stderr matched: 'Motoi cannot connect to networks. Ever.'
  4. lib/net/etsy-fetcher.js — REJECTED as generic net-file violation         PASS
     - stderr matched: 'new file under lib/net/ (not on allow-list)'
     - stderr matched: 'Sakura'
  5. src/foo.js — fetch(\"https://…\") REJECTED                               PASS
     - stderr matched: 'source lines that shape like an HTTP client'
     - stderr matched: 'remote HTTP fetch|remote URL string literal'
  6. src/foo.js — fetch(\"http://localhost:8080\") ALLOWED (loopback)         PASS
  7. lib/ai/llm.js — exempt (curl to local model endpoint OK)                 PASS
  8. comments containing http:// are ignored                                  PASS
  9. axios import in src/ REJECTED                                            PASS

Live install-verification (per the task's Install section):
  1. Staged a synthetic `lib/net/test-client.js` containing a fetch() to
     a remote URL.
  2. Ran `bash .githooks/pre-commit`.
     -> exit 1
     -> stderr showed BOTH the LOAM-flavored net-file violation AND the
        HTTP-client source-line violation, correctly citing the file and
        both matched patterns.
  3. Unstaged and deleted the probe file. lib/net/ back to
     [http-serve.js] only. No commit was made."

  :known-limitations
"1. Bash regex approach. The hook depends on bash + grep + sed + awk being
   present. Fine on macOS/Linux dev boxes; would need reconsidering on a
   pure Windows path (this repo is macOS/Linux only, per Alfred's stack).

2. String-literal detection is heuristic. Something like
     const url = 'http' + '://api.example.com'
   splits the URL across concatenation and slips through. The hook is a
   TRIP-WIRE for the common, honest cases (loam-client, axios import,
   fetch(http…)), not a formal capability sandbox. A determined evader
   who wants to violate doctrine can. This is intentional — the hook
   is aimed at the good-faith agent that forgot, not the adversary.

3. `--no-verify` is undetectable from inside the hook. Alfred's rule stands:
   don't use it. No further defense possible at this layer.

4. The hook only scans .js/.mjs/.cjs/.ts/.mts/.cts extensions. If someone
   authors a shell script under lib/ that curls a remote URL, this hook
   will NOT catch it. Extension list can be widened later; deferred until
   there's a real case."

  :durable-notes
"When adding a new pre-commit check, extend .githooks/pre-commit rather than
adding a second file — a single hook file keeps the fast path in one place
and avoids duplicated git-diff work.

If a legitimate new file needs to live under lib/net/ (some future SERVER
counterpart), add its basename to the NET_ALLOW=(...) array near the top of
the hook and add a fixture to tests/hooks/pre-commit.test.mjs.

Do not weaken Guard 2's remote-URL check without Alfred's explicit sign-off.
That's the doctrine-load-bearing rule."

  :composed-with
    ((:doctrine "project_motoi_no_tools_no_internet_2026_07_17")
     (:doctrine "project_sakura_internet_business_posture_2026_07_17")
     (:doctrine "project_stop_fake_completion_cycle_2026_07_16")
     (:archive  "_archive-doctrine-violation-loam-client-2026-07-17/MANIFEST.slat"))

  :status "shipped")
